Meanwhile, I apply temporary restart or scaling.â€
â“Q4: What is Load Average? How do you interpret it?
âœ… Answer:
â€œLoad average shows average number of runnable or waiting processes in 1, 5, and 15 minutes.
If load is higher than CPU cores, system is overloaded.
I correlate load with CPU and I/O metrics.â€
